    • Constructor Detail

      • CuckooMap2

        public CuckooMap2()
        Creates a new, empty CuckooMap2 using a default family of universal hash functions. Note that this is in general NOT SAFE unless you can positively guarantee that no two distinct objects have distinct hash codes. This will be true for objects that don't explicitly override hashCode(), and certain numeric wrappers like Integer, but not for more complex types like String.
